name: Scenes from a Venetian Carnival by Chris Bickford

metadata.name: Dream
metadata.description: Carnival is a subversive fantasy, a dream of Dionysian abandon and collective mayhem. We are attracted to the dream, but do we dare to live it? The dream lives on, written in our DNA. Rituals of disguise and abandon proliferate in almost every human culture. All it takes is a little imagination and a disguise to pour your fantasies into. The theater of Venice provides the backdrop.
